CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 19, 1969, pg. 1, reads: "Plea to Police Vandalized - Neighborhood youths are shown Tuesday as they worked to again put up the large sign on a vacant lot at Columbo and Aiken Aves. in Garfield Hill Section of the city which had been knocked down Monday, in some mysterious manner after the Garfield Teen-Age Organization, headed by Emmanuel Gay had constructed it and set it up. Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Men gathered around sign reading "Police.. We need your protection... not your harassment, Garfield Teen Organization," on Columbo Avenue, Garfield
